OL,4,Cunveiled for the first time
OL,6,FSince discovering the archive, Oliver
OL,7,Fhas been reading his grandfather
OL,8,Faccount of the day, he reads: "Swarms
OL,9,Fof gliders of the sixth airborne
OL,10,Fdivision were seen to be approaching
OL,11,Fand we were amazed to see them landing
OL,12,Fall around us, sometimes too close for
OL,13,Fcomfort.
OL,15,F"The gliders were followed by mass of
OL,16,Ftransports dropping containers
OL,17,Fcontaining arms and supplies. And the
OL,18,Fair was soon thick with coloured
OL,19,Fparachutes."
