OL,4,Cunveiled for the first time
OL,6,FMajor Brock's children discovered the
OL,7,Fpipe had a significant meaning, Oliver
OL,8,Fexplains: "I remember being on a
OL,9,Ffamily holiday in Caen and he was
OL,10,Flooking at a pigsty and he said 'this
OL,11,Fwas where I found a couple of Germans
OL,12,Fand I kind of waved my pipe at them,
OL,13,Fthey thought it was a pistol so they
OL,14,Fsurrendered'."
OL,16,FBut Oliver says if he had discovered
OL,17,Fthat his Grandpa was involved in D-Day
OL,18,Fwhen he was alive, he would not have
OL,19,Fspoken about it.
